    "body": "### Problem\n\nCommit c8dbb04da96dd200165690cba253c8b832bc388a (`vim-patch:9.2.0510`) introduced a regression where pressing `<CR>` inside a bracket pair in insert mode no longer expands correctly when a plugin uses `setline()` as part of a `<CR>` insert-mode mapping (specifically `nvim-autopairs` with `map_cr = true`).\n\nInstead of the expected expansion:\n```\n{|}  →  {\n          |\n        }\n```\n\nThe cursor is placed **after** the closing bracket:\n```\n{|}  →  {\n        }\n        |\n```\n\nThis is caused by the autoindent-stripping logic change in the patch — the condition `Only strip autoindent whitespace when the rest of the line is all whitespace` now fires during `setline()`-based CR mappings in a way that displaces the closing bracket line, corrupting the expansion.\n\nBisected to: `c8dbb04da96dd200165690cba253c8b832bc388a` — regression not present in `v0.12.2`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Install [[nvim-autopairs](https://github.com/windwp/nvim-autopairs)](https://github.com/windwp/nvim-autopairs) with the following minimal config (`nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`):\n\n```lua\n-- minimal.lua\nvim.opt.rtp:prepend('/path/to/nvim-autopairs')  -- adjust path\nrequire('nvim-autopairs').setup({ map_cr = true })\n```\n\n2. Open a `.lua` file:\n```\n:edit test.lua\n```\n3. Enter insert mode, type `{`, which auto-closes to `{}`\n4. Press `<CR>` with cursor between `{` and `}`\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCursor lands on an indented new line between the brackets:\n```\n{\n    |\n}\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev (commit c8dbb04da96dd200165690cba253c8b832bc388a)\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNot tested — this is a Neovim-specific regression introduced by a vim-patch backport.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux (Linux 6.18.21-1-lts x86_64)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.46.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBuilt from source (`git clone` + `make CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release`)",
